Calculate ride duration

trip2022 <- trip2022 %>% 
  mutate (ride_duration = ended_at - started_at)

Parse month, hour, week day information

trip2022 <- trip2022 %>% 
  mutate (month = month(started_at, label=TRUE)) %>%
  mutate (start_hour = hour(started_at)) %>%
  mutate (weekday = wday(started_at, label=TRUE))

Export data file

##remove less useful columns and export as csv file
trip2022[-c(6, 8:12)] %>% write.csv("Google_Data/Case_Study_1/Trip_data/2022_trip_data.csv")

Summary of total number and duration of trips

all_trip <- trip2022 %>%
  group_by (member_casual) %>%
  summarise(total_trip = n(), total_duration = sum(ride_duration), median_duration = median(ride_duration)) %>% 
  mutate(total_duration_days = day(seconds_to_period(total_duration))) %>%
  mutate (median_trip_duration_min = minute(seconds_to_period(median_duration))) %>%
  select (member_casual,total_trip,total_duration_days,median_trip_duration_min)
all_trip

Plot total number of ride by month and type of user

trip2022 %>% group_by(month, member_casual) %>% 
  summarise(total_trip=n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=month, y=total_trip)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  facet_grid (col = vars(member_casual)) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, size = 10)) +
  ggtitle("Number of rides during 2022") +
  ylab("Number of rides")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'month'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.

Plot total trip duration

trip2022 %>% group_by(month, member_casual) %>% 
  summarise(total_duration=sum(ride_duration)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=month, y=total_duration)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  facet_grid (col = vars(member_casual)) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, size = 10)) +
  ggtitle("Total Ride Time during 2022") +
  ylab("Ride Duration (sec)")

## Plot bike type usage info

trip2022 %>% group_by(month,member_casual,rideable_type) %>%
  summarise(type = n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=month, y=type, fill=rideable_type)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") + ylab("Number of ride") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, size = 10)) +
  facet_grid(cols = vars(member_casual))

Plot usage data by days of the week

## Number of trips
trip2022 %>% group_by(weekday,member_casual) %>% 
  summarise(total_trip=n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=weekday, y=total_trip)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  facet_grid(cols = vars(member_casual)) +
  ggtitle("Ride number by days of the week") +
  ylab("Number of trips")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'weekday'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.

## Duration of trips
trip2022 %>% group_by(weekday, member_casual) %>% 
  summarise(median_duration=median(ride_duration)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=weekday, y=median_duration)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  facet_grid(cols = vars(member_casual)) +
  ggtitle("Ride Duration by Days of the Week") + ylab("Median Ride Duration (sec)")

Plot ride location data of members during morning peak hours (7-8 am)

# Start Stations
trip2022 %>% 
  filter (weekday == c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri"), member_casual == "member", start_hour == c(7,8)) %>%
  group_by(start_station_name) %>%
  summarise(total=n()) %>%
  na.omit(start_station_name) %>%
  filter(total > 150) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=start_station_name, y=total)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  ggtitle("Start stations used by members between 7-8 am during weekdays") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, size = 9)) +
  ylab("Number of rides")
## Warning: There were 3 warnings in `filter()`.
## The first warning was:
## ℹ In argument: `weekday == c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri")`.
